-- Bogdanka, KGHM Polska Miedz: Central Europe Equity Preview
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-01-19T07:30:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/bogdanka-kghm-polska-miedz-central-europe-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  rose 0.9 percent, the Czech  PX Index (PX) 
climbed 1.5 percent and Hungary’s  BUX Index (BUX)  gained 3 percent.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)  : Labor unions at KGHM,
Poland’s sole copper producer, will decide tomorrow on a protest
against the Polish government’s plan to introduce a new copper
tax, Parkiet reported.  KGHM will hold a general meeting today to vote on a plan to
buy back as much as 3 billion zloty of shares and elect new
members of the supervisory board. The shares rose 1.3 percent to
130.2 zloty.  Lubelski Wegiel Bogdanka SA (LWB)  : Poland’s second-
biggest publicly traded coal producer, may sign an agreement to
deliver coal to  Enea SA (ENA) , Dziennik Gazeta Prawna reported today,
without saying where it got the information. The agreement could
be valued at as much as 15 billion zloty ($4.44 billion) at
current prices, the newspaper said.  Bogdanka shares lost 0.1 percent to 109.3 zloty and Enea
stock gained 0.8 percent to 18.3 zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
